Rating: 3
this was super easy to make....I didn't have pine nuts so I just used 2 +1/4c almonds. Also, didn't have cake flour so I used whole wheat pastry flour and it seemed to work fine. Also, I dusted 1/2 of them with cinnamon (generously) before baking. They turned out good enough!

Rating: 4
Excellent and simple recipe. I didn't have pine nuts so I subbed more almonds and I reduced sugar by 1/4 cup. I think I made mine a nit bigger than they are supposed to be so they took over 15 mins to cook. They are brown on the bottom and so soft and chewy inside...even better the next day. I'll make these again for sure even if they are "ugly".

